This pattern is consistent with real-world 1.21.1 Architectury workspaces and is the minimal ÔÇťplumbingÔÇŁ needed for plugin resolution and module inclusion. ţłÇciteţłéturn12view1ţłéturn16view0ţłü

### Example root `build.gradle` for Minecraft 1.21.1

This root script demonstrates three ideas the official docs keep returning to:
- declare the Architectury plugins at the root and apply Loom to subprojects, ţłÇciteţłéturn16view0ţłéturn14search2ţłü
- configure mappings in a consistent way, because remapping is fundamental to Loom-based modding, ţłÇciteţłéturn16view0ţłü
- enforce Java 21 compilation for 1.21-era builds (NeoForge explicitly requires a Java 21 JDK as a prerequisite, and many 1.21.1 workspaces compile with release 21). ţłÇciteţłéturn20search10ţłéturn12view0ţłü

```gradle
plugins {
    id "architectury-plugin" version "3.4-SNAPSHOT"
    id "dev.architectury.loom" version "1.9.428" apply false
}

architectury {
    minecraft = rootProject.minecraft_version
}

subprojects {
    apply plugin: "dev.architectury.loom"

    loom {
        silentMojangMappingsLicense()
    }

    dependencies {
        minecraft "com.mojang:minecraft:${rootProject.minecraft_version}"
        mappings loom.officialMojangMappings()
    }
}

allprojects {
    apply plugin: "java"
    apply plugin: "architectury-plugin"
    apply plugin: "maven-publish"

    group = rootProject.maven_group
    version = rootProject.mod_version

    tasks.withType(JavaCompile).configureEach {
        options.encoding = "UTF-8"
        options.release = 21
    }

    java {
        withSourcesJar()
    }
}
```

The overall shape (root plugin declarations, `architectury { minecraft = ... }`, Loom applied in subprojects, Java 21 release) matches the structure used by 1.21.1 Architectury builds. ţłÇciteţłéturn12view0ţłü

